The paper deals with a problem of coordinating multiple robots to achieve a common goal, which is a common theme in multi-agent systems (cs.MA) and robotics (cs.RO). The problem involves searching and evacuating from a disk, which can be seen as a problem in computational geometry (cs.CG) or distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also proposes an algorithm for the problem, which can be seen as a contribution to algorithm design and analysis (cs.DS). Finally, the problem involves communication and coordination among the robots, which can be seen as a problem in control systems (cs.SY).
